author: ehillenius
msg: Instead, the nested example is extended with a much more simpler example of a tree. It uses the FlatTree implementation which is now the default tree of Wicket.

author: ehillenius
msg: Moved ListTree to contrib. The ListTree is usable in certain cases, however the

FlatTree is both easier to work with and is currently more usable as it reacts to both junction and node clicks. The same is probably possible for ListTree, but nesting and using links in HTML is a problem. So, the FlatTree will be the default tree for Wicket and will be (more) actively supported.
